data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. Unique opportunity to own a piece of Isle of Pines/Moss Park history. What started out as a commercial property was a bait store to supply local fish camps in the mid 1900s, turned into the famous Isle of Pines Country Store in 1984. When the development of Lake Nona came to town, the store could not sustain. At that time it was transformed into a home. The home is nestled on a very sought after 2 acres of pristine land within the very desirable Isle of Pines. The current home is 1 bedroom 1.5 bath. Large 20x22 screened rear porch to sit and enjoy the nature that the Isle of Pines has to offer. The Isle of Pines is a very unique community and joining the optional HOA grants you access to the private park with boat ramp, dock, beach and swimming area, playground, basketball court, restrooms and a pavilion that you can reserve for your own private functions at no extra expense. The community sponsors many holiday gatherings for you to socialize and get to know your neighbors. Truly like stepping back in time. Also within the community is Orange County's Isle of Pines Preserve for all of your hiking and equestrian needs or just a nice stroll to the lake through the natural Florida landscape. Located minutes to everything that Lake Nona has to offer and local highways for easy access to International Airport, Area Attractions, UCF, Lake Nona's Medical City, VA, Boxi Park, Downtown Orlando or a short ride to area beaches. With 2 acres of real estate within the rural settlement of the Isle of pines, this is a very rare opportunity to step back in time, let your imagination run wild, and make this everything that you ever dreamed of. The current RC-E zoning allows for things such as adult/child care, Air B&B, seasonal sales such as Christmas trees or pumpkins.  This property was originally plotted as 3 separate lots. With the ability to re-divide, the potential for this property is only limited to what the mind desires.
